description:
Add a test in core/src/messages.rs that constructs the old JSON format manually and verifies serde_json::from_str rejects it cleanly:
```
let old_format = r#"{"action":"request","chain":"zcash","amount":"0.1"}"#;
let result: Result<PaymentAction, _> = serde_json::from_str(old_format);
assert!(result.is_err(), "old string format must be rejected");
```
Oracle: serde with #[serde(deny_unknown_fields)] or missing required field causes an error.
